item.title: Milwaukee Tour
item.description: Known for its beer, brats, baseball, and stunning lakefront scenery, Milwaukee is a town with a lot more sights than most travelers realize. During the course of this Milwaukee sightseeing tour, see the city's famous City Hall and tour the Milwaukee Art Museum. Learn the history of this city by the lake and view its exceptional homes, and since tours are capped at 14 people you're ensured a personalized experience.

image.alt: Milwaukee Tour

item.title: Discover Iconic Milwaukee Tour
item.description: Swap the big bus tours for a crowd-free experience. Traveling in an open-air, five-seater electric vehicle, you'll thoroughly explore the historic city of Milwaukee, from popular tourist destinations to some hidden gems that most visitors miss. As you travel, your guide will fill you in on Milwaukee's rich and exciting history. This tour has different lengths to suit your schedule.

image.alt: Discover Iconic Milwaukee Tour

item.title: Milwaukee Walking Food Tour With Secret Food Tours
item.description: The Midwestern city of Milwaukee is known for its beer and cheese and this walking food tour gives you a taste of the best. Join a small group and enjoy a walk through "Brew City" to sample a number of beers and regional snacks. Learn about the 19th-century Germanic population that immigrated to the area and its influence on today's local cuisine.

image.alt: Milwaukee Walking Food Tour With Secret Food Tours

item.title: Brew City Ghosts: Macabre Milwaukee By US Ghost Adventures
item.description: Unveil the dark history of Brew City with this ghost tour of the city’s most haunted locations. Meet your guide for a ghoul-fueled stroll through the heart of Milwaukee to take in spirit-infested historic hotels, theaters, and even skyscrapers. Be entertained by bone-chilling ghost stories and tales of paranormal activity as you delve into Milwaukee’s ghoulish past.

image.alt: Brew City Ghosts: Macabre Milwaukee By US Ghost Adventures

item.title: Shakers Original Historical Ghost Tour
item.description: One of the most haunted bars in the nation, Shaker’s Cigar Bar—a Milwaukee institution—has a history as wild as its ghostly encounters. On this small-group tour, you’ll explore behind the scenes, hearing stories about the Capone brothers and Jeffrey Dahmer, the bar's cemetery and brothel past, and more. Bring your camera, sure, but beware of what you might catch on film.

image.alt: Shakers Original Historical Ghost Tour

item.title: Cream City Cannibal: Jeffery Dahmer Walking Tour
item.description: As seen on the BBC, yes, that BBC. this tour is so gruesome, that NBC called it the " Tour of Terror" and NETFLIX picked this tour as one of the eight most unique adventure tours in the world for a new series: "Dark Tourist". Not for the faint of heart! The Cream City Cannibal Tour has been featured in the John Borowski film; Serial Killer Culture and used by regional University Psychology and Criminal Justice departments. Walk in the exact footsteps of cannibalistic serial killer Jeffrey Dahmer, where he poached 7 of his 17 victims. Rife with tales of caution, psychological dissection, and terrifying details, the Cream City Cannibal is not for the feint of heart. Outdoor, Rain or Shine.

image.alt: Cream City Cannibal: Jeffery Dahmer Walking Tour

item.title: Skip the Line: Museum Admission Ticket - Grohmann Museum
item.description: Prebook this Grohmann Museum Skip-the-Line Admission Ticket to bypass the lines at the museum on the busy school campus and head inside to explore its collections and exhibits. The museum showcases the art of labor, engineering, and human achievement while and offering a unique display you won’t find anywhere else. This admission ticket is perfect for groups that want to explore but who are also on a budget.

image.alt: Skip the Line: Museum Admission Ticket - Grohmann Museum

item.title: The Grand Walk: A Self-Guided Audio Tour through Milwaukee
item.description: The home of American lager and once a rival to Chicago in size, Milwaukee’s history and preeminence may not be as obvious as it once was—unless you look. With this self-guided audio tour, you’ll travel down Brew City’s most opulent drag, from the Milwaukee Public Library to the Milwaukee Art Museum. Across 150 years of history and plenty of steps, you’ll get a guided-tour experience without any of the crowds.

image.alt: The Grand Walk: A Self-Guided Audio Tour through Milwaukee

item.title: Milwaukee Private or Public Pedal Tavern Tour
item.description:
Tour an upcoming and historic neighborhood just on the outside of downtown like a local would! Local and friendly drivers to take you along our well-known route.
Experience a unique way to travel around with pedal power! Fun and different experience on the tavern as you cheer your crew, and make memories and friends along the scenic river and downtown! 21+ Tour

image.alt: Milwaukee Private or Public Pedal Tavern Tour

item.title: Shakers Ghost Tour 2.0
item.description: Shakers Bar in Milwaukee has some gritty stories that have happened behind its walls. This ghost tour explains all the details, and at the same time summons the spirits. Enjoy this experience with a small-group, where you might make a few new friends. Another perk is that you can use a divination rod, made more special by sipping an included cocktail.

image.alt: Shakers Ghost Tour 2.0

item.title: Original Milwaukee Guided Brewery Tour with Lunch or Dinner
item.description:
Guests will learn about Milwaukee’s thriving brewpub scene and visit four separate breweries, tasting up to 16 different beers on this guided brewery tour with a snack.
Visit some of Milwaukee's most popular brewpubs, including Lakefront Brewing, Broken Bat Brewing Co, Ope!, Gathering Place, and Wizard Works, to name a few. Round trip transportation by bus in downtown Milwaukee is included.
Please try to book your tour at least 72 hours in advance of the tour to confirm availability. Tours book up quickly, and tours booked inside this window may not have room.

image.alt: Original Milwaukee Guided Brewery Tour with Lunch or Dinner

item.title: Sip of Milwaukee Guided Brewery Tour with Snack
item.description:
Learn about Milwaukee’s thriving brewpub scene and taste up to 12 different beers on this guided brewery tour with a snack. See how beer is made and chat with brewery owners about their operations. Visit some of MKE’s most popular breweries, including Pilot Project, Perspective Brewing, and Dead Bird, to name a few. Round-trip transportation by bus in downtown Milwaukee is included.
Please try to book your tour at least 72 hours in advance of the tour to confirm availability. Tours book up quickly, and tours booked inside this window may not have room.

image.alt: Sip of Milwaukee Guided Brewery Tour with Snack

item.title: Sheboygan Arts & Water Segway Tour w/ Private Tour Option
item.description: Explore Sheboygan’s highlights in a fun way, on a Segway, on this small-group excursion. Cruise along the Sheboygan River and Lake Michigan shoreline to see the lighthouse, shipwreck sites, schooner remains, and the John Michael Kohler Arts Center. If you’d like, you can upgrade to a private tour for a more personalized experience.

image.alt: Sheboygan Arts & Water Segway Tour w/ Private Tour Option

item.title: Magical Milwaukee Scavenger Hunt
item.description: Discover the highlights and hidden secrets of Milwaukee without having to read a guidebook on this fun and interactive scavenger hunt. Even though it’s a self-guided hunt, the package includes a remote host to chat to and get support from along the way. With your group, work as a team to solve clues and explore the city’s unusual oddities, local hotspots, and hidden surprises.

image.alt: Magical Milwaukee Scavenger Hunt

item.title: 2 Hour Sailing Adventure in Lake Michigan (up to 6 people)
item.description: Set sail around Lake Michigan on this private adventure tour. With the safety of a life jacket and boat captain, spend two hours enjoying a smooth sail along the calming waters, soaking up city views of Milwaukee, Kenosha, and Racine. You also have the opportunity to spot local wildlife like lake trout, sandhill cranes, and otters.

image.alt: 2 Hour Sailing Adventure in Lake Michigan (up to 6 people)

item.title: Downtown Kenosha Urban Art and Photography Walking Tour
item.description:
Our tour blends art, street art, architecture and history to provide an informative yet interesting tour. You will be provided excellent views of Lake Michigan and various photography spots for those who love to take pictures. Our goal is to keep prices low while still offering a quality product that is fun for the entire family.
The comfort and ease of having everything organized for you takes away the stress when going on holiday. Plus, the extra support and experience of a guide and the chance to travel with and meet like-minded people makes this tour much more attractive.
Kenosha is an exciting and vibrant community on the shores of Lake Michigan in Southeastern, Wisconsin. Come enjoy the history and art that make up the Downtown and Harbor Park communities.

image.alt: Downtown Kenosha Urban Art and Photography Walking Tour

item.title: Small Group Kayak Tour of Skyline in Milwaukee
item.description: Our guided City Skyline Kayak Tours are 1.5–2 hours long and follow the Milwaukee River up towards downtown Milwaukee. We do not make any stops along the way for this tour, but we do provide details about Milwaukee's history and attractions along the river. Our knowledgeable guides will provide you with any kayaking instruction you may need and ensure you feel safe and comfortable on this beginner-level tour.

image.alt: Small Group Kayak Tour of Skyline in Milwaukee

item.title: Self-Guided Scavenger Hunt: Milwaukee A Splash of Color
item.description: See the sights of Milwaukee while learning facts about the city on an entertaining and interactive scavenger hunt. This app-based game will lead you through the city, challenging you with trivia questions and tasks as you pursue the items on your list. This is a fun group activity for team building, parties, or anyone looking for a playful and memorable way to get to know Milwaukee.

image.alt: Self-Guided Scavenger Hunt: Milwaukee A Splash of Color

item.title: Private Metal Detecting Tour to Simmons Island Beach of Kenosha
item.description:
We all know the benefits of exercise: a healthier heart, stronger bones, improved circulation, and flexibility. The hobby of metal detecting can be both rewarding and enjoyable at the same time. The hobby is fun and has been around for decades and is becoming more and more accessible for everyone to try. People who metal detect find many interesting items, from coins to relics and everything in between.
Come enjoy this family friendly tour that is perfect for all ages. We make it easy and simple, just bring the family and let us take care of the rest.

image.alt: Private Metal Detecting Tour to Simmons Island Beach of Kenosha

item.title: Private Downtown Milwaukee Helicopter Ride
item.description: The Milwaukee Downtown ride takes you on a on an exhilarating helicopter journey down the Milwaukee Bay where you can witness Downtown Milwaukee like never before! This ride offers a truly unique perspective, soaring directly over the heart of the city. You’ll be treated to sweeping views of the Milwaukee River, the iconic Hoan Bridge, and the majestic Milwaukee Art Museum. But that’s not all – this ride encompasses the entire cityscape, ensuring you don’t miss a single landmark.

image.alt: Private Downtown Milwaukee Helicopter Ride

item.title: Waukesha Ghost Walks
item.description: Experience the spooky side of Waukesha while exploring the town on foot with this walking tour, which focuses on haunted history and lore. Meet your guide at the entrance to the Waukesha Riverwalk and head out on the town, visiting ghostly spots such as Cutler Park, Carroll College, and more.

image.alt: Waukesha Ghost Walks

item.title: Milwaukee Brewers Baseball Game Ticket at American Family Field
item.description:
Experiencing the Milwaukee Brewers play a Major League Baseball game live at American Family Field is something that all baseball fans should experience. The ballpark is always filled with excited and passionate fans cheering on their favourite team from the first pitch to the last out. From the unique Wisconsin favourites that are served as concession stand offerings to the wide variety of souvenirs available, this historic stadium provides an unmatched atmosphere for any baseball fan. Whether you’re looking to take in a game with friends or family, attending a game at American Family Field is sure to be an unforgettable experience!
To ensure you get the best seats, tickets are sourced from a combination of primary and reseller partners and are perfect for travelers, guaranteeing seamless access to the venue. Premium & Regular category seats generally sit along the 3rd or 1st baseline with Premium seats closer to the field. Budget seating is typically in higher tiers in the outfield.

image.alt: Milwaukee Brewers Baseball Game Ticket at American Family Field

item.title: Private Tour: Secret Food Tours Milwaukee
item.description:
Milwaukee is called many names; Brew City, City of Festivals, and Cream City, but it is most recognized as the place for great beer and cheese in the Upper Midwest. The large 19th century Germanic population continue to influence our local food products and dishes while some of the best restaurants from the historic Third Ward to East Town Downtown. When booking our winter exclusive Skywalk Food Tour you'll get to experience and enjoy all the best we have to offer from a warm second-story perspective. You'll get to experience and enjoy all the best we have when you book our Secret Food Tour: Milwaukee.
As a private tour, everything works around you! Our start times are much more easy going, dates can open up. It's a much more intimate and cozy experience. No need to shout over other tourists, you will have every question answered, and leave feeling like a native yourself!

image.alt: Private Tour: Secret Food Tours Milwaukee

item.title: Luxury Car Arrival from Milwaukee Airport MKE to Milwaukee City
item.description: Simplify your arrival in Milwaukee with a private transfer from Milwaukee Mitchell International Airport to your hotel in the city. Fly confidently, knowing you’ll be met at the airport. Travel in a comfortable business-level car, which is ideal for corporate and leisure travelers alike. Sit back and enjoy the ride into the city and arrive feeling ready to explore Milwaukee.

image.alt: Luxury Car Arrival from Milwaukee Airport MKE to Milwaukee City
